# Vanilla Plugin Development

## When to use
- Building custom plugins or widgets for Spotify's Vanilla community
- Adding new React widgets to the Layout Editor
- Creating custom API endpoints
- Understanding Vanilla's addon/plugin architecture
- Injecting custom HTML/JS via Pockets

## Plugin Structure

```
plugins/<plugin-name>/
  addon.json                           # Plugin manifest
  <PluginName>Plugin.php               # Main plugin class (legacy) OR:
  Addon/<PluginName>ContainerRules.php # DI container wiring (modern)
  Controllers/
    Api/<Name>ApiController.php        # REST API endpoints
    <Name>Controller.php               # Page controllers
  Library/
    <WidgetName>.php                   # Widget classes
  src/scripts/
    entries/
      forum.tsx                        # Forum-facing JS entry
      admin-new.tsx                    # Admin layout editor entry
      layouts.tsx                      # Layout widget registration
    components/widgets/
      <WidgetName>.tsx                 # React widget component
      <WidgetName>.module.scss         # Scoped styles
      <WidgetName>Preview.tsx          # Layout editor preview
  locale/
    en.php                             # English strings
  tests/
    <Name>Tests.php                    # PHPUnit tests
  openapi/<name>.yml                   # OpenAPI spec (optional)
```

### addon.json

```json
{
  "key": "my-spotify-plugin",
  "name": "Spotify Custom Plugin",
  "description": "Custom functionality for Spotify Community",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "addon",
  "require": {
    "vanilla": ">=2024.001"
  },
  "sites": ["6038735.vanillacommunities.com"],
  "icon": "my-icon.svg",
  "settingsUrl": "/settings/my-plugin",
  "settingsRoute": "/settings/my-plugin"
}
```

Key fields:
- `sites` — restrict plugin to specific site domains (omit for all sites)
- `require` — version constraints
- `settingsUrl` — admin settings page URL

## Widget Development (Layout Editor)

The key pattern for adding visual components. Three pieces must match:

### 1. PHP Widget Class

```php
<?php
namespace Vanilla\MyPlugin;

use Vanilla\Widgets\React\ReactWidgetInterface;
use Vanilla\Layout\LayoutHydrator;

class MyWidget implements ReactWidgetInterface {

    public static function getComponentName(): string {
        return "MyWidget";  // Must match JS component name exactly
    }

    public static function getWidgetIconPath(): string {
        return "/plugins/my-plugin/design/my-icon.svg";
    }

    public static function getWidgetSchema(): Schema {
        return Schema::parse([
            "title:s?" => ["description" => "Widget title", "x-control" => SchemaForm::textBox()],
            "maxItems:i?" => ["description" => "Max items", "default" => 5, "x-control" => SchemaForm::dropDown(
                new FormOptions("Max Items"),
                new StaticFormChoices(["3" => "3", "5" => "5", "10" => "10"])
            )],
        ]);
    }

    public static function getWidgetName(): string {
        return "My Custom Widget";
    }

    public function getProps(): ?array {
        return ["title" => "Default Title", "maxItems" => 5];
    }
}
```

### 2. Container Rules (register with Layout Hydrator)

```php
<?php
namespace Vanilla\MyPlugin\Addon;

use Garden\Container\ContainerConfigurationInterface;
use Vanilla\Layout\LayoutHydrator;

class MyPluginContainerRules {
    public function configureContainer(ContainerConfigurationInterface $container): void {
        $container->rule(LayoutHydrator::class)
            ->addCall("addReactResolver", [MyWidget::class]);
    }
}
```

### 3. TypeScript Widget Component

**entries/layouts.tsx** (widget registration):
```tsx
import { registerLoadableWidgets } from "@library/utility/componentRegistry";

registerLoadableWidgets({
    MyWidget: () => import("../components/widgets/MyWidget"),
});
```

**entries/admin-new.tsx** (layout editor preview):
```tsx
import { registerWidgetOverviews } from "@dashboard/layout/editor/widgetSettings/WidgetSettingsModal";
import MyWidgetPreview from "../components/widgets/MyWidgetPreview";

registerWidgetOverviews({
    MyWidget: MyWidgetPreview,
});
```

**components/widgets/MyWidget.tsx**:
```tsx
import React from "react";

interface IMyWidgetProps {
    title?: string;
    maxItems?: number;
}

export default function MyWidget(props: IMyWidgetProps) {
    const { title = "Default", maxItems = 5 } = props;
    return (
        <div className="myWidget">
            <h2>{title}</h2>
            {/* Widget content */}
        </div>
    );
}
```

**The component name string must be identical** in `getComponentName()`, `registerLoadableWidgets`, and `registerWidgetOverviews`.

## API Controllers

```php
<?php
namespace Vanilla\MyPlugin\Controllers\Api;

use AbstractApiController;
use Garden\Schema\Schema;
use Garden\Web\Data;

class MyApiController extends AbstractApiController {

    // GET /api/v2/my-endpoint
    public function index(array $query): Data {
        $this->permission(); // No specific permission = any authenticated user
        $in = $this->schema(Schema::parse(["limit:i?" => ["default" => 10]]), "in");
        $query = $in->validate($query);

        return new Data(["items" => []], ["paging" => ["totalCount" => 0]]);
    }

    // GET /api/v2/my-endpoint/:id
    public function get(int $id): Data {
        $this->permission("site.manage"); // Requires admin
        return new Data(["id" => $id]);
    }

    // POST /api/v2/my-endpoint
    public function post(array $body): Data {
        $this->permission("myPlugin.manage");
        $in = $this->schema(Schema::parse(["name:s", "value:s?"]), "in");
        $body = $in->validate($body);

        return new Data($body, 201);
    }
}
```

Schema validation uses `garden-schema`. The controller name minus "ApiController" becomes the URL path (e.g., `MyApiController` -> `/api/v2/my`).

## PHP Event Hooks (Legacy Pattern)

```php
class MyPlugin extends Gdn_Plugin {
    // Fires before every page render
    public function base_render_before($sender) {
        $sender->addJsFile('custom.js', 'plugins/my-plugin/js');
    }

    // Fires when a discussion is saved
    public function discussionModel_afterSaveDiscussion_handler($sender, $args) {
        $discussionID = $args['DiscussionID'];
        // Custom logic
    }

    // Fires when viewing a category
    public function categoriesController_render_before($sender) {
        $categoryID = $sender->data('Category.CategoryID');
    }

    // Plugin setup (activation)
    public function setup() {
        // Run on first enable
    }

    // Plugin structure (runs on every config change)
    public function structure() {
        // Create/alter DB tables
        Gdn::structure()
            ->table('MyTable')
            ->column('MyTableID', 'int', false, 'primary')
            ->column('Name', 'varchar(100)')
            ->set();
    }
}
```

## Pockets (No-Code HTML Injection)

The Pockets plugin lets admins inject HTML/JS into named slots without writing a plugin. Access via dashboard Settings > Pockets.

Available locations:
- `Head` — inside `<head>` (for meta tags, tracking scripts)
- `Content` — before/after main content
- `Panel` — sidebar slots
- `Foot` — before `</body>`
- `BetweenDiscussions` — between discussion list rows
- `BetweenComments` — between comment rows

Good for: analytics tags, promotional banners, cookie consent, custom CSS injection.

## Widget Fragments (Extending Core Widgets)

Fragments let you extend existing core widgets without replacing them:

```php
class MyFragmentMeta extends SiteTotalsFragmentMeta {
    public function getFragmentKey(): string {
        return "myFragment";
    }

    public static function getSchema(): Schema {
        return Schema::parse([
            "callToActionText:s?" => ["default" => "Join Now"],
        ]);
    }
}
```

```tsx
// Injectable interface
export interface IMyFragment {
    callToActionText?: string;
}

// Template component
export function MyFragment(props: IMyFragment) {
    return <a href="/register">{props.callToActionText ?? "Join Now"}</a>;
}
```

## SSO Integration

Two main SSO plugins included in vanilla-local:

### jsconnect (Vanilla's native SSO)
- JWT-based, supports cross-domain
- Partner implements a jsconnect endpoint that returns user data
- Config: `$Configuration['Plugins']['jsconnect']`

### OAuth2
- Generic OAuth2 flow
- Config: client ID, secret, authorize URL, token URL, profile URL
- Plugin key: `oauth2`

