## Key Patterns from Spotify-trial

### Personalised Banner (role-based CTA)
Shows different content based on user role:
- Guest: "Become a Star" CTA
- Member: "Apply Now" CTA
- Star role: "Visit the Backstage" CTA
Uses `useCurrentUserSignedIn()` and role checking from Vanilla's React hooks.

### Section Class Widget (CSS injection)
Zero-height widget that injects a CSS class onto its parent layout section DOM node. Enables per-section theming via CSS without writing section-specific widgets.

### Body Class Provider (URL-based theming)
Maps URL paths to body CSS classes, supporting subcommunity prefixes:
```tsx
const PAGE_CLASS_MAP: Record<string, string> = {
    "stars-home": "page-stars-home",
    "star-apply": "page-star-apply",
    "leaderboard": "page-leaderboard",
};
```

### Personalised Feed (interest weighting)
Discussion list widget that reads `interestWeights` from user profile fields and applies as sort weighting. Hooks into `/api/v2/discussions` index schema to add `?spotifyFeed=true` filter. Currently a stub/POC.
